    <item>
      <title>Re: Can any Cleric do this??</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&amp;message.id=10669#M10669</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
thumex&amp;nbsp;wrote:&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Cleric's DS stacked is 79..correct. Though, any cleric that pulls 3-4 mobs at a time to use the Ward efficiently has to cast on EACH mob. Since the spell is designed as a reverse DS. It is very mana inefficient.&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;I hope you meant Mark and not Ward here.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;If you are re-casting Ward of Vengeance/Retribution 4 times if you are fighting 4 mobs, then yes you are using mana inefficiently. The Ward spells are self buffs and are active against all monsters that may be taking a swing at you.&amp;nbsp; You don't have to targe anyone with this spell. It is self-only.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Marks of course operate as you indicated.&amp;nbsp; I don't find them terribly mana inefficient though. When you look at the damage being done to the mobs over a fight, and compare it to the mana you'd use nuking, the numbers quickly add up in favour of the damage shields.&amp;nbsp; Look at the numbers from my bazu thrasher fight.&amp;nbsp; Damage shields did over 16k damage in the span of&amp;nbsp; 3 minutes.&amp;nbsp; Now, that includes me casting Mark of Retribution, Mark of the Blameless, as well as using a Kilva's Skin of Flame potion and the clickie effect from my Blazing Vambraces.&amp;nbsp; The monster hit me around 133 times during the fight, and took over 100hp each time they did so.&amp;nbsp; Ouch.&amp;nbsp; That's a good use of mana, I'd say. (parser is reporting 2 damage shield hits per successful monster attack -- one is the "regular" damage shield, the other is the "reverse" damage shield.)&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
brum wrote:&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Still only getting about one proc for every 11 or 12 times of getting hit.&amp;nbsp; getting hit only--worse if you count the misses.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; I have misses turned off but go back after fight and look at how many times i get hit vs how many times proc of ward goes off.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; so including misses would be much worse even.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Have used it on about 16 or so mobs now and that is best I have gotten so dont believe it is just run of bad luck anymore.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I have dex maxxed.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; what else can I do to make it proc more?&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; are there any AAs that help?&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; cause currently this spell seems a waste.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;As Thaere said, spellcasting fury.&amp;nbsp; If you want to solo, I cannot encourage you enough to max out all of your Spellcasting Fury lines (Gift of Mana helps a lot too).&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; With Mark of Retribution alone, you are doing 550 damage when the ward goes off.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; I have Spellcasting Fury 3, Fury of Magic 3, Fury of Magic Mastery 3, and Destructive Fury 3. A regular ward hit still goes off for 550; a crit goes off for 1237 though, which is a remarkable improvement. Destructive Fury 3 is not as important as getting all the levels in the previous three AA abilities. Those are the ones that increase your chance to land a critical nuke.&amp;nbsp; Of course those should always be secondary to your healing &amp;amp; survival AAs, but they are nonetheless important for any cleric who wants to solo.&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Looking at my Bazu Thrasher fight again, I got 29 procs total (this number includes weapon and Ward procs); fight took three minutes, so if I knock off 6 procs (one each minute for both of the procs on my main weapon), I'm still looking at 23 over 3 minutes; monster hit me 133 times and missed 68; looking at those numbers, I'm getting a Ward proc in every 8-9 swings, which isn't that far off of your numbers.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;While there are no AAs that will directly increase our proc rates (we'd need Weapon Affinity or something like that, I believe), the AAs that can indirectly help are the various Fury AAs, as well as your stat increase AAs (I know you said you had dex maxed out, but is that just with your current cap, or do you still have AAs to put into Planar Power &amp;amp; Chaotic Potential?) &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;If you are indeed maxed in all these areas, then I don't know what else to say. This spell changed the way I solo and drastically increases the variety of targets I can consider as viable solo options. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
