      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;Well.. I decided to head to Wall of Slaughter today for a little bit. I set up at the south wall, near a few corpses from an earlier failed group (none of the members were online at the time, and their resurrection timers were quite old). and after slaying a feran, a chimera and a bazu thrasher, guess who should appear but the Bazu Bonesmasher.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;So.. I medded up to full, got my buffs ready, and waited for the Bonesmasher to wander back towards me. I attempted to stun him ( my usual technique for getting Mark of the Blameless on the mob and ensuring I can run back to a safe spot before the monster catches up to me) but he resisted; I got rooted a little ways away from my usual spot, but cleared it with Purify Soul and managed to get back to my usual spot.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I had used Greater Avatar against a bazu earlier, so that was unavailable to me, but I cast Celestial Rejuvenation on myself and went about trying to kill the Bonesmasher. However (another example of bad planning), my Ward of Retribution wore off around the bonesmasher's 70% mark, and my Clarity X potion wore off shortly thereafter too.&amp;nbsp; It was all I could do to keep myself alive for a few moments while I tried to work in a cast of Ward and a reclick of the mana potion.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I finally managed to get both back on, and I felt I was doing quite well.&amp;nbsp; Mana was around 30%, and the bonesmasher was around 35%.&amp;nbsp; However, a passing warrior happened by, and seeing an apparently alone cleric and several slain groupmates, he fired off one of his high-damage disciplines and started hacking away. End result, I got credit for the kill, although I think I only did about half of the monster's remaining 30% health.&amp;nbsp; I'm not 100% certain I would have won the fight entirely solo, but I'm fairly certain I still would have won, without the warrior's intervention. At no point did I lose aggro, until the bonesmasher fled with low health.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;The bonesmasher yielded a bazu plasma, a minor muramite rune and a tainted heartstone charm.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;BR&gt;So... I'll be going back, and I hope to get a "pure" solo kill. I'm sure I'll get it next time.. and I'll be sure to recast Ward of Retribution just before I engage!&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
