s soloing hard mobs: ghetto summon kiting with elixir up is a great way to "med".&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Anyway, back to the point of the post.  Anything a druid can solo, a cleric can solo.  And clerics can solo for decent xp in certain places.  I make 4aa/hour solo in chardokb, which is more than most classes get solo, so we can't really complain about not being able to solo.  So all in all, I think clerics are the most powerful solo class in the game right now (comparing both xp gain and difficulty of mobs we can solo), but we are extremely gear dependant on soloing.  In contrast, my necro with like 4k mana can solo for 5aa/hour without breaking a sweat, though he'd get owned by any mob that can summon.</description>
