&lt;DIV&gt;Thaere, my failure was on the Bazu Bonesmasher, a named bazu that paths around the south wall area.&amp;nbsp; It's not trash (the Bonesmasher is level 68, according to Alla's bestiary, while the 'trash' bazus are level 64).&amp;nbsp; That was the one I struggled with (and eventually died to).&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;However, I spent a large part of my day yesterday soloing with some success in Wall of Slaughter, at the south wall camp and also in the entry tunnel between WoS and Noble's Causeway.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; I had a few tradeskill drops (bazu blood, various level skins, trean flies, some gems, a Kuuan Lodestone, and an icy shard) and generally had a lot of fun.&amp;nbsp; I mostly enjoyed it for the challenge, but also for the (somewhat small) chance of decent loot, even from the non-nameds. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;The running mobs are certainly a problem, but if you are careful you can pull them far enough from the main wandering area so that you can finish them off before they get far enough to aggro something else.&amp;nbsp; When the monsters turned to run, I'd stun them ASAP then root them.&amp;nbsp; I'd try and channel a nuke through after they summoned me and kept hitting me; with Ward still active, usually root would break relatively quickly and I'd get a nuke off; the monster would now be around 10% or lower and quite a bit slower.&amp;nbsp; Repeat with another root (or stun if it's refreshed), another nuke, and by then it was usually a simple matter to finish them off.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;The experience was not on par to what I can earn in Hate or even Veksar (since the fights take a lot more out of me) but for challenge and fun, they can't be beat.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Two days and I still haven't seen the Bonesmasher again, or any of the weaker nameds, but when I&amp;nbsp; do I'll post an update as to my success -- or failure.&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
